main event: A sighting of an unidentified object in the sky over Kenema, Sierra Leone on November 27, 1963.
interesting points: The object was observed traveling at great speed and appeared to be surrounded by a rain-drift., The light emitted from the object was described as supernatural with a large bright halo., The sound associated with the object resembled many people walking in the distance., The sighting lasted approximately 20 minutes., The object was later identified as being related to the launching of an Atlas Meteor Satellite.
sighted object: unidentified object with a supernatural light
witness description: Reported by an individual who observed the object closely.
